&lt;p&gt;Would you like an opportunity to work in our Women’s Cancer Services as a Nurse Specialist? This is an excellent opportunity if you are an experienced nurse looking to enhance your skills in supporting patients across their whole cancer pathway. Gynaecology and Breast Cancer services have merged to become the Women’s Cancer service and so this is an exciting time to make a contribution to the further development of this passionate and dynamic Specialist Nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who can demonstrate they have experience in caring and supporting patients and their families and enabling them to make informed decisions. You must be able to demonstrate you have the necessary communication and organisational skills and have an understanding of the current cancer agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to supporting you in your development in this specialty, and as such recognise the right candidate may not yet have the full remit of skills required. For informal discussions regarding the post please contact either Marion Webb, Team leader for the Women’s Cancer service on 01423 555732 or Noreen Hawkshaw Lead Cancer Nurse Tel 01423 555797&lt;/p&gt;
